3773void DisassemblingDecoder::ProcessOutput(Instruction* /*instr*/) {
3774 // The base disasm does nothing more than disassembling into a buffer.
3775}
3776
3777void DisassemblingDecoder::AppendRegisterNameToOutput(const CPURegister& reg) {
3778 DCHECK(reg.is_valid());
3779 char reg_char;
3780
3781 if (reg.IsRegister()) {
3782 reg_char = reg.Is64Bits() ? 'x' : 'w';
3783 } else {
3784 DCHECK(reg.IsVRegister());
3785 switch (reg.SizeInBits()) {
3786 case kBRegSizeInBits:
3787 reg_char = 'b';
3788 break;
3789 case kHRegSizeInBits:
3790 reg_char = 'h';
3791 break;
3792 case kSRegSizeInBits:
3793 reg_char = 's';
3794 break;
3795 case kDRegSizeInBits:
3796 reg_char = 'd';
3797 break;
3798 default:
3799 DCHECK(reg.Is128Bits());
3800 reg_char = 'q';
3801 }
3802 }
3803
3804 if (reg.IsVRegister() || !(reg.Aliases(sp) || reg.Aliases(xzr))) {
3805 // Filter special registers
3806 if (reg.IsX() && (reg.code() == 27)) {
3807 AppendToOutput("cp");
3808 } else if (reg.IsX() && (reg.code() == 29)) {
3809 AppendToOutput("fp");
3810 } else if (reg.IsX() && (reg.code() == 30)) {
3811 AppendToOutput("lr");
3812 } else {
3813 // A core or scalar/vector register: [wx]0 - 30, [bhsdq]0 - 31.
3814 AppendToOutput("%c%d", reg_char, reg.code());
3815 }
3816 } else if (reg.Aliases(sp)) {
3817 // Disassemble w31/x31 as stack pointer wsp/sp.
3818 AppendToOutput("%s", reg.Is64Bits() ? "sp" : "wsp");
3819 } else {
3820 // Disassemble w31/x31 as zero register wzr/xzr.
3821 AppendToOutput("%czr", reg_char);
3822 }
3823}
3824
3825void DisassemblingDecoder::Format(Instruction* instr, const char* mnemonic,
3826 const char* format) {
3827 // TODO(mcapewel) don't think I can use the instr address here - there needs
3828 // to be a base address too
3829 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(mnemonic);
3830 ResetOutput();
3831 Substitute(instr, mnemonic);
3832 if (format != nullptr) {
3833 buffer_[buffer_pos_++] = ' ';
3834 Substitute(instr, format);
3835 }
3836 buffer_[buffer_pos_] = 0;
3837 ProcessOutput(instr);
3838}
3839
3840void DisassemblingDecoder::Substitute(Instruction* instr, const char* string) {
3841 char chr = *string++;
3842 while (chr != '\0') {
3843 if (chr == '\'') {
3844 string += SubstituteField(instr, string);
3845 } else {
3846 buffer_[buffer_pos_++] = chr;
3847 }
3848 chr = *string++;
3849 }
3850}
3851
3852int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteField(Instruction* instr,
3853 const char* format) {
3854 switch (format[0]) {
3855 // NB. The remaining substitution prefix characters are: GJKUZ.
3856 case 'R': // Register. X or W, selected by sf bit.
3857 case 'F': // FP register. S or D, selected by type field.
3858 case 'V': // Vector register, V, vector format.
3859 case 'W':
3860 case 'X':
3861 case 'B':
3862 case 'H':
3863 case 'S':
3864 case 'D':
3865 case 'Q':
3866 return SubstituteRegisterField(instr, format);
3867 case 'I':
3868 return SubstituteImmediateField(instr, format);
3869 case 'L':
3870 return SubstituteLiteralField(instr, format);
3871 case 'N':
3872 return SubstituteShiftField(instr, format);
3873 case 'P':
3874 return SubstitutePrefetchField(instr, format);
3875 case 'C':
3876 return SubstituteConditionField(instr, format);
3877 case 'E':
3878 return SubstituteExtendField(instr, format);
3879 case 'A':
3880 return SubstitutePCRelAddressField(instr, format);
3881 case 'T':
3882 return SubstituteBranchTargetField(instr, format);
3883 case 'O':
3884 return SubstituteLSRegOffsetField(instr, format);
3885 case 'M':
3886 return SubstituteBarrierField(instr, format);
3887 default:
3888 UNREACHABLE();
3889 }
3890}
3891
3892int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteRegisterField(Instruction* instr,
3893 const char* format) {
3894 char reg_prefix = format[0];
3895 unsigned reg_num = 0;
3896 unsigned field_len = 2;
3897
3898 switch (format[1]) {
3899 case 'd':
3900 reg_num = instr->Rd();
3901 if (format[2] == 'q') {
3902 reg_prefix = instr->NEONQ() ? 'X' : 'W';
3903 field_len = 3;
3904 }
3905 break;
3906 case 'n':
3907 reg_num = instr->Rn();
3908 break;
3909 case 'm':
3910 reg_num = instr->Rm();
3911 switch (format[2]) {
3912 // Handle registers tagged with b (bytes), z (instruction), or
3913 // r (registers), used for address updates in
3914 // NEON load/store instructions.
3915 case 'r':
3916 case 'b':
3917 case 'z': {
3918 field_len = 3;
3919 char* eimm;
3920 int imm = static_cast<int>(strtol(&format[3], &eimm, 10));
3921 field_len += eimm - &format[3];
3922 if (reg_num == 31) {
3923 switch (format[2]) {
3924 case 'z':
3925 imm *= (1 << instr->NEONLSSize());
3926 break;
3927 case 'r':
3928 imm *= (instr->NEONQ() == 0) ? kDRegSize : kQRegSize;
3929 break;
3930 case 'b':
3931 break;
3932 }
3933 AppendToOutput("#%d", imm);
3934 return field_len;
3935 }
3936 break;
3937 }
3938 }
3939 break;
3940 case 'e':
3941 // This is register Rm, but using a 4-bit specifier. Used in NEON
3942 // by-element instructions.
3943 reg_num = (instr->Rm() & 0xF);
3944 break;
3945 case 'a':
3946 reg_num = instr->Ra();
3947 break;
3948 case 't':
3949 reg_num = instr->Rt();
3950 if (format[0] == 'V') {
3951 if ((format[2] >= '2') && (format[2] <= '4')) {
3952 // Handle consecutive vector register specifiers Vt2, Vt3 and Vt4.
3953 reg_num = (reg_num + format[2] - '1') % 32;
3954 field_len = 3;
3955 }
3956 } else {
3957 if (format[2] == '2') {
3958 // Handle register specifier Rt2.
3959 reg_num = instr->Rt2();
3960 field_len = 3;
3961 }
3962 }
3963 break;
3964 case 's':
3965 reg_num = instr->Rs();
3966 break;
3967 default:
3968 UNREACHABLE();
3969 }
3970
3971 // Increase field length for registers tagged as stack.
3972 if (format[2] == 's') {
3973 field_len = 3;
3974 }
3975
3976 // W or X registers tagged with '+' have their number incremented, to support
3977 // instructions such as CASP.
3978 if (format[2] == '+') {
3979 DCHECK((reg_prefix == 'W') || (reg_prefix == 'X'));
3980 reg_num++;
3981 field_len++;
3982 }
3983
3984 CPURegister::RegisterType reg_type;
3985 unsigned reg_size;
3986
3987 if (reg_prefix == 'R') {
3988 reg_prefix = instr->SixtyFourBits() ? 'X' : 'W';
3989 } else if (reg_prefix == 'F') {
3990 reg_prefix = ((instr->FPType() & 1) == 0) ? 'S' : 'D';
3991 }
3992
3993 switch (reg_prefix) {
3994 case 'W':
3995 reg_type = CPURegister::kRegister;
3996 reg_size = kWRegSizeInBits;
3997 break;
3998 case 'X':
3999 reg_type = CPURegister::kRegister;
4000 reg_size = kXRegSizeInBits;
4001 break;
4002 case 'B':
4003 reg_type = CPURegister::kVRegister;
4004 reg_size = kBRegSizeInBits;
4005 break;
4006 case 'H':
4007 reg_type = CPURegister::kVRegister;
4008 reg_size = kHRegSizeInBits;
4009 break;
4010 case 'S':
4011 reg_type = CPURegister::kVRegister;
4012 reg_size = kSRegSizeInBits;
4013 break;
4014 case 'D':
4015 reg_type = CPURegister::kVRegister;
4016 reg_size = kDRegSizeInBits;
4017 break;
4018 case 'Q':
4019 reg_type = CPURegister::kVRegister;
4020 reg_size = kQRegSizeInBits;
4021 break;
4022 case 'V':
4023 AppendToOutput("v%d", reg_num);
4024 return field_len;
4025 default:
4026 UNREACHABLE();
4027 }
4028
4029 if ((reg_type == CPURegister::kRegister) && (reg_num == kZeroRegCode) &&
4030 (format[2] == 's')) {
4031 reg_num = kSPRegInternalCode;
4032 }
4033
4034 AppendRegisterNameToOutput(CPURegister::Create(reg_num, reg_size, reg_type));
4035
4036 return field_len;
4037}
4038
4039int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteImmediateField(Instruction* instr,
4040 const char* format) {
4041 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'I');
4042
4043 switch (format[1]) {
4044 case 'M': { // IMoveImm or IMoveLSL.
4045 if (format[5] == 'I' || format[5] == 'N') {
4046 uint64_t imm = static_cast<uint64_t>(instr->ImmMoveWide())
4047 << (16 * instr->ShiftMoveWide());
4048 if (format[5] == 'N') imm = ~imm;
4049 if (!instr->SixtyFourBits()) imm &= UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF);
4050 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64, imm);
4051 } else {
4052 DCHECK_EQ(format[5], 'L');
4053 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64, instr->ImmMoveWide());
4054 if (instr->ShiftMoveWide() > 0) {
4055 AppendToOutput(", lsl #%d", 16 * instr->ShiftMoveWide());
4056 }
4057 }
4058 return 8;
4059 }
4060 case 'L': {
4061 switch (format[2]) {
4062 case 'L': { // ILLiteral - Immediate Load Literal.
4063 AppendToOutput("pc%+" PRId32,
4064 instr->ImmLLiteral() * kLoadLiteralScale);
4065 return 9;
4066 }
4067 case 'S': { // ILS - Immediate Load/Store.
4068 if (instr->ImmLS() != 0) {
4069 AppendToOutput(", #%" PRId32, instr->ImmLS());
4070 }
4071 return 3;
4072 }
4073 case 'P': { // ILPx - Immediate Load/Store Pair, x = access size.
4074 if (instr->ImmLSPair() != 0) {
4075 // format[3] is the scale value. Convert to a number.
4076 int scale = 1 << (format[3] - '0');
4077 AppendToOutput(", #%" PRId32, instr->ImmLSPair() * scale);
4078 }
4079 return 4;
4080 }
4081 case 'U': { // ILU - Immediate Load/Store Unsigned.
4082 if (instr->ImmLSUnsigned() != 0) {
4083 int shift = instr->SizeLS();
4084 AppendToOutput(", #%" PRId32, instr->ImmLSUnsigned() << shift);
4085 }
4086 return 3;
4087 }
4088 }
4089 }
4090 case 'C': { // ICondB - Immediate Conditional Branch.
4091 int64_t offset = instr->ImmCondBranch() << 2;
4092 char sign = (offset >= 0) ? '+' : '-';
4093 AppendToOutput("#%c0x%" PRIx64, sign, offset);
4094 return 6;
4095 }
4096 case 'A': { // IAddSub.
4097 DCHECK_LE(instr->ShiftAddSub(), 1);
4098 int64_t imm = instr->ImmAddSub() << (12 * instr->ShiftAddSub());
4099 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64 " (%" PRId64 ")", imm, imm);
4100 return 7;
4101 }
4102 case 'F': { // IFPSingle, IFPDouble or IFPFBits.
4103 if (format[3] == 'F') { // IFPFBits.
4104 AppendToOutput("#%d", 64 - instr->FPScale());
4105 return 8;
4106 } else {
4107 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx32 " (%.4f)", instr->ImmFP(),
4108 format[3] == 'S' ? instr->ImmFP32() : instr->ImmFP64());
4109 return 9;
4110 }
4111 }
4112 case 'T': { // ITri - Immediate Triangular Encoded.
4113 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64, instr->ImmLogical());
4114 return 4;
4115 }
4116 case 'N': { // INzcv.
4117 int nzcv = (instr->Nzcv() << Flags_offset);
4118 AppendToOutput("#%c%c%c%c", ((nzcv & NFlag) == 0) ? 'n' : 'N',
4119 ((nzcv & ZFlag) == 0) ? 'z' : 'Z',
4120 ((nzcv & CFlag) == 0) ? 'c' : 'C',
4121 ((nzcv & VFlag) == 0) ? 'v' : 'V');
4122 return 5;
4123 }
4124 case 'P': { // IP - Conditional compare.
4125 AppendToOutput("#%d", instr->ImmCondCmp());
4126 return 2;
4127 }
4128 case 'B': { // Bitfields.
4129 return SubstituteBitfieldImmediateField(instr, format);
4130 }
4131 case 'E': { // IExtract.
4132 AppendToOutput("#%d", instr->ImmS());
4133 return 8;
4134 }
4135 case 'S': { // IS - Test and branch bit.
4136 AppendToOutput("#%d", (instr->ImmTestBranchBit5() << 5) |
4137 instr->ImmTestBranchBit40());
4138 return 2;
4139 }
4140 case 's': { // Is - Shift (immediate).
4141 switch (format[2]) {
4142 case '1': { // Is1 - SSHR.
4143 int shift = 16 << HighestSetBitPosition(instr->ImmNEONImmh());
4144 shift -= instr->ImmNEONImmhImmb();
4145 AppendToOutput("#%d", shift);
4146 return 3;
4147 }
4148 case '2': { // Is2 - SLI.
4149 int shift = instr->ImmNEONImmhImmb();
4150 shift -= 8 << HighestSetBitPosition(instr->ImmNEONImmh());
4151 AppendToOutput("#%d", shift);
4152 return 3;
4153 }
4154 default: {
4155 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4156 }
4157 }
4158 }
4159 case 'D': { // IDebug - HLT and BRK instructions.
4160 AppendToOutput("#0x%x", instr->ImmException());
4161 return 6;
4162 }
4163 case 'V': { // Immediate Vector.
4164 switch (format[2]) {
4165 case 'E': { // IVExtract.
4166 AppendToOutput("#%" PRId64, instr->ImmNEONExt());
4167 return 9;
4168 }
4169 case 'B': { // IVByElemIndex.
4170 int vm_index = (instr->NEONH() << 1) | instr->NEONL();
4171 if (instr->NEONSize() == 1) {
4172 vm_index = (vm_index << 1) | instr->NEONM();
4173 }
4174 AppendToOutput("%d", vm_index);
4175 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVByElemIndex"));
4176 }
4177 case 'I': { // INS element.
4178 if (strncmp(format, "IVInsIndex", strlen("IVInsIndex")) == 0) {
4179 unsigned rd_index, rn_index;
4180 unsigned imm5 = instr->ImmNEON5();
4181 unsigned imm4 = instr->ImmNEON4();
4182 int tz = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(imm5);
4183 if (tz <= 3) { // Defined for 0 <= tz <= 3 only.
4184 rd_index = imm5 >> (tz + 1);
4185 rn_index = imm4 >> tz;
4186 if (strncmp(format, "IVInsIndex1", strlen("IVInsIndex1")) == 0) {
4187 AppendToOutput("%d", rd_index);
4188 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVInsIndex1"));
4189 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVInsIndex2",
4190 strlen("IVInsIndex2")) == 0) {
4191 AppendToOutput("%d", rn_index);
4192 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVInsIndex2"));
4193 }
4194 }
4195 return 0;
4196 }
4197 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4198 }
4199 case 'L': { // IVLSLane[0123] - suffix indicates access size shift.
4200 AppendToOutput("%d", instr->NEONLSIndex(format[8] - '0'));
4201 return 9;
4202 }
4203 case 'M': { // Modified Immediate cases.
4204 if (strncmp(format, "IVMIImmFPSingle", strlen("IVMIImmFPSingle")) ==
4205 0) {
4206 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx32 " (%.4f)", instr->ImmNEONabcdefgh(),
4207 instr->ImmNEONFP32());
4208 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIImmFPSingle"));
4209 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVMIImmFPDouble",
4210 strlen("IVMIImmFPDouble")) == 0) {
4211 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx32 " (%.4f)", instr->ImmNEONabcdefgh(),
4212 instr->ImmNEONFP64());
4213 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIImmFPDouble"));
4214 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVMIImm8", strlen("IVMIImm8")) == 0) {
4215 uint64_t imm8 = instr->ImmNEONabcdefgh();
4216 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64, imm8);
4217 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIImm8"));
4218 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVMIImm", strlen("IVMIImm")) == 0) {
4219 uint64_t imm8 = instr->ImmNEONabcdefgh();
4220 uint64_t imm = 0;
4221 for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
4222 if (imm8 & (1ULL << i)) {
4223 imm |= (UINT64_C(0xFF) << (8 * i));
4224 }
4225 }
4226 AppendToOutput("#0x%" PRIx64, imm);
4227 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIImm"));
4228 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVMIShiftAmt1",
4229 strlen("IVMIShiftAmt1")) == 0) {
4230 int cmode = instr->NEONCmode();
4231 int shift_amount = 8 * ((cmode >> 1) & 3);
4232 AppendToOutput("#%d", shift_amount);
4233 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIShiftAmt1"));
4234 } else if (strncmp(format, "IVMIShiftAmt2",
4235 strlen("IVMIShiftAmt2")) == 0) {
4236 int cmode = instr->NEONCmode();
4237 int shift_amount = 8 << (cmode & 1);
4238 AppendToOutput("#%d", shift_amount);
4239 return static_cast<int>(strlen("IVMIShiftAmt2"));
4240 } else {
4241 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4242 }
4243 }
4244 default: {
4245 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4246 }
4247 }
4248 }
4249 default: {
4250 printf("%s", format);
4251 UNREACHABLE();
4252 }
4253 }
4254}
4255
4256int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteBitfieldImmediateField(Instruction* instr,
4257 const char* format) {
4258 DCHECK((format[0] == 'I') && (format[1] == 'B'));
4259 unsigned r = instr->ImmR();
4260 unsigned s = instr->ImmS();
4261
4262 switch (format[2]) {
4263 case 'r': { // IBr.
4264 AppendToOutput("#%d", r);
4265 return 3;
4266 }
4267 case 's': { // IBs+1 or IBs-r+1.
4268 if (format[3] == '+') {
4269 AppendToOutput("#%d", s + 1);
4270 return 5;
4271 } else {
4272 DCHECK_EQ(format[3], '-');
4273 AppendToOutput("#%d", s - r + 1);
4274 return 7;
4275 }
4276 }
4277 case 'Z': { // IBZ-r.
4278 DCHECK((format[3] == '-') && (format[4] == 'r'));
4279 unsigned reg_size =
4280 (instr->SixtyFourBits() == 1) ? kXRegSizeInBits : kWRegSizeInBits;
4281 AppendToOutput("#%d", reg_size - r);
4282 return 5;
4283 }
4284 default: {
4285 UNREACHABLE();
4286 }
4287 }
4288}
4289
4290int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteLiteralField(Instruction* instr,
4291 const char* format) {
4292 DCHECK_EQ(strncmp(format, "LValue", 6), 0);
4293 USE(format);
4294
4295 switch (instr->Mask(LoadLiteralMask)) {
4296 case LDR_w_lit:
4297 case LDR_x_lit:
4298 case LDR_s_lit:
4299 case LDR_d_lit:
4300 AppendToOutput("(addr 0x%016" PRIxPTR ")", instr->LiteralAddress());
4301 break;
4302 default:
4303 UNREACHABLE();
4304 }
4305
4306 return 6;
4307}
4308
4309int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteShiftField(Instruction* instr,
4310 const char* format) {
4311 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'N');
4312 DCHECK_LE(instr->ShiftDP(), 0x3);
4313
4314 switch (format[1]) {
4315 case 'D': { // NDP.
4316 DCHECK(instr->ShiftDP() != ROR);
4317 [[fallthrough]];
4318 }
4319 case 'L': { // NLo.
4320 if (instr->ImmDPShift() != 0) {
4321 const char* shift_type[] = {"lsl", "lsr", "asr", "ror"};
4322 AppendToOutput(", %s #%" PRId32, shift_type[instr->ShiftDP()],
4323 instr->ImmDPShift());
4324 }
4325 return 3;
4326 }
4327 default:
4328 UNREACHABLE();
4329 }
4330}
4331
4332int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteConditionField(Instruction* instr,
4333 const char* format) {
4334 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'C');
4335 const char* condition_code[] = {"eq", "ne", "hs", "lo", "mi", "pl",
4336 "vs", "vc", "hi", "ls", "ge", "lt",
4337 "gt", "le", "al", "nv"};
4338 int cond;
4339 switch (format[1]) {
4340 case 'B':
4341 cond = instr->ConditionBranch();
4342 break;
4343 case 'I': {
4344 cond = NegateCondition(static_cast<Condition>(instr->Condition()));
4345 break;
4346 }
4347 default:
4348 cond = instr->Condition();
4349 }
4350 AppendToOutput("%s", condition_code[cond]);
4351 return 4;
4352}
4353
4354int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstitutePCRelAddressField(Instruction* instr,
4355 const char* format) {
4356 USE(format);
4357 DCHECK_EQ(strncmp(format, "AddrPCRel", 9), 0);
4358
4359 int offset = instr->ImmPCRel();
4360
4361 // Only ADR (AddrPCRelByte) is supported.
4362 DCHECK_EQ(strcmp(format, "AddrPCRelByte"), 0);
4363
4364 char sign = '+';
4365 if (offset < 0) {
4366 sign = '-';
4367 }
4368 AppendToOutput("#%c0x%x (addr %p)", sign, Abs(offset),
4369 instr->InstructionAtOffset(offset, Instruction::NO_CHECK));
4370 return 13;
4371}
4372
4373int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteBranchTargetField(Instruction* instr,
4374 const char* format) {
4375 DCHECK_EQ(strncmp(format, "TImm", 4), 0);
4376
4377 int64_t offset = 0;
4378 switch (format[5]) {
4379 // TImmUncn - unconditional branch immediate.
4380 case 'n':
4381 offset = instr->ImmUncondBranch();
4382 break;
4383 // TImmCond - conditional branch immediate.
4384 case 'o':
4385 offset = instr->ImmCondBranch();
4386 break;
4387 // TImmCmpa - compare and branch immediate.
4388 case 'm':
4389 offset = instr->ImmCmpBranch();
4390 break;
4391 // TImmTest - test and branch immediate.
4392 case 'e':
4393 offset = instr->ImmTestBranch();
4394 break;
4395 default:
4396 UNREACHABLE();
4397 }
4398 offset *= kInstrSize;
4399 char sign = '+';
4400 if (offset < 0) {
4401 sign = '-';
4402 }
4403 AppendToOutput("#%c0x%" PRIx64 " (addr %p)", sign, Abs(offset),
4404 instr->InstructionAtOffset(offset), Instruction::NO_CHECK);
4405 return 8;
4406}
4407
4408int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteExtendField(Instruction* instr,
4409 const char* format) {
4410 DCHECK_EQ(strncmp(format, "Ext", 3), 0);
4411 DCHECK_LE(instr->ExtendMode(), 7);
4412 USE(format);
4413
4414 const char* extend_mode[] = {"uxtb", "uxth", "uxtw", "uxtx",
4415 "sxtb", "sxth", "sxtw", "sxtx"};
4416
4417 // If rd or rn is SP, uxtw on 32-bit registers and uxtx on 64-bit
4418 // registers becomes lsl.
4419 if (((instr->Rd() == kZeroRegCode) || (instr->Rn() == kZeroRegCode)) &&
4420 (((instr->ExtendMode() == UXTW) && (instr->SixtyFourBits() == 0)) ||
4421 (instr->ExtendMode() == UXTX))) {
4422 if (instr->ImmExtendShift() > 0) {
4423 AppendToOutput(", lsl #%d", instr->ImmExtendShift());
4424 }
4425 } else {
4426 AppendToOutput(", %s", extend_mode[instr->ExtendMode()]);
4427 if (instr->ImmExtendShift() > 0) {
4428 AppendToOutput(" #%d", instr->ImmExtendShift());
4429 }
4430 }
4431 return 3;
4432}
4433
4434int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteLSRegOffsetField(Instruction* instr,
4435 const char* format) {
4436 DCHECK_EQ(strncmp(format, "Offsetreg", 9), 0);
4437 const char* extend_mode[] = {"undefined", "undefined", "uxtw", "lsl",
4438 "undefined", "undefined", "sxtw", "sxtx"};
4439 USE(format);
4440
4441 unsigned shift = instr->ImmShiftLS();
4442 Extend ext = static_cast<Extend>(instr->ExtendMode());
4443 char reg_type = ((ext == UXTW) || (ext == SXTW)) ? 'w' : 'x';
4444
4445 unsigned rm = instr->Rm();
4446 if (rm == kZeroRegCode) {
4447 AppendToOutput("%czr", reg_type);
4448 } else {
4449 AppendToOutput("%c%d", reg_type, rm);
4450 }
4451
4452 // Extend mode UXTX is an alias for shift mode LSL here.
4453 if (!((ext == UXTX) && (shift == 0))) {
4454 AppendToOutput(", %s", extend_mode[ext]);
4455 if (shift != 0) {
4456 AppendToOutput(" #%d", instr->SizeLS());
4457 }
4458 }
4459 return 9;
4460}
4461
4462int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstitutePrefetchField(Instruction* instr,
4463 const char* format) {
4464 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'P');
4465 USE(format);
4466
4467 int prefetch_mode = instr->PrefetchMode();
4468
4469 const char* ls = (prefetch_mode & 0x10) ? "st" : "ld";
4470 int level = (prefetch_mode >> 1) + 1;
4471 const char* ks = (prefetch_mode & 1) ? "strm" : "keep";
4472
4473 AppendToOutput("p%sl%d%s", ls, level, ks);
4474 return 6;
4475}
4476
4477int DisassemblingDecoder::SubstituteBarrierField(Instruction* instr,
4478 const char* format) {
4479 DCHECK_EQ(format[0], 'M');
4480 USE(format);
4481
4482 static const char* const options[4][4] = {
4483 {"sy (0b0000)", "oshld", "oshst", "osh"},
4484 {"sy (0b0100)", "nshld", "nshst", "nsh"},
4485 {"sy (0b1000)", "ishld", "ishst", "ish"},
4486 {"sy (0b1100)", "ld", "st", "sy"}};
4487 int domain = instr->ImmBarrierDomain();
4488 int type = instr->ImmBarrierType();
4489
4490 AppendToOutput("%s", options[domain][type]);
4491 return 1;
4492}
4493
4494void DisassemblingDecoder::ResetOutput() {
4495 buffer_pos_ = 0;
4496 buffer_[buffer_pos_] = 0;
4497}
4498
4499void DisassemblingDecoder::AppendToOutput(const char* format, ...) {
4500 va_list args;
4501 va_start(args, format);
4502 buffer_pos_ += vsnprintf(&buffer_[buffer_pos_], buffer_size_, format, args);
4503 va_end(args);
4504}
4505
4506void DisassemblingDecoder::DisassembleNEONPolynomialMul(Instruction* instr) {
4507 int q = instr->Bit(30);
4508 const char* mnemonic = q ? "pmull2" : "pmull";
4509 const char* form = NULL;
4510 int size = instr->NEONSize();
4511 if (size == 0) {
4512 if (q == 0) {
4513 form = "'Vd.8h, 'Vn.8b, 'Vm.8b";
4514 } else {
4515 form = "'Vd.8h, 'Vn.16b, 'Vm.16b";
4516 }
4517 } else if (size == 3) {
4518 if (q == 0) {
4519 form = "'Vd.1q, 'Vn.1d, 'Vm.1d";
4520 } else {
4521 form = "'Vd.1q, 'Vn.2d, 'Vm.2d";
4522 }
4523 } else {
4524 mnemonic = "undefined";
4525 }
4526 Format(instr, mnemonic, form);
4527}

4529void PrintDisassembler::ProcessOutput(Instruction* instr) {
4530 fprintf(stream_, "0x%016" PRIx64 " %08" PRIx32 "\t\t%s\n",
4531 reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(instr), instr->InstructionBits(),
4532 GetOutput());
4533}

4540const char* NameConverter::NameOfAddress(uint8_t* addr) const {
4541 v8::base::SNPrintF(tmp_buffer_, "%p", static_cast<void*>(addr));
4542 return tmp_buffer_.begin();

4548
4549const char* NameConverter::NameOfCPURegister(int reg) const {
4550 unsigned ureg = reg; // Avoid warnings about signed/unsigned comparisons.
4551 if (ureg >= v8::internal::kNumberOfRegisters) {
4552 return "noreg";
4553 }
4554 if (ureg == v8::internal::kZeroRegCode) {
4555 return "xzr";
4556 }
4557 v8::base::SNPrintF(tmp_buffer_, "x%u", ureg);
4558 return tmp_buffer_.begin();
4559}
4560
4561const char* NameConverter::NameOfByteCPURegister(int reg) const {
4562 UNREACHABLE(); // ARM64 does not have the concept of a byte register
4563}
4564
4565const char* NameConverter::NameOfXMMRegister(int reg) const {
4566 UNREACHABLE(); // ARM64 does not have any XMM registers
4567}

4569const char* NameConverter::NameInCode(uint8_t* addr) const {
4570 // The default name converter is called for unknown code, so we will not try
4571 // to access any memory.
4572 return "";
4573}

4577class BufferDisassembler : public v8::internal::DisassemblingDecoder {
4578 public:
4579 explicit BufferDisassembler(v8::base::Vector<char> out_buffer)
4580 : out_buffer_(out_buffer) {}
4581
4582 ~BufferDisassembler() {}
4583
4584 virtual void ProcessOutput(v8::internal::Instruction* instr) {
4585 v8::base::SNPrintF(out_buffer_, "%08" PRIx32 " %s",
4586 instr->InstructionBits(), GetOutput());
4587 }
4588
4589 private:
4590 v8::base::Vector<char> out_buffer_;
4591};
4592
4593int Disassembler::InstructionDecode(v8::base::Vector<char> buffer,
4594 uint8_t* instr) {
4595 USE(converter_); // avoid unused field warning
4596 v8::internal::Decoder<v8::internal::DispatchingDecoderVisitor> decoder;
4597 BufferDisassembler disasm(buffer);
4598 decoder.AppendVisitor(&disasm);
4599
4600 decoder.Decode(reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Instruction*>(instr));
4601 return v8::internal::kInstrSize;
4602}
4603
4604int Disassembler::ConstantPoolSizeAt(uint8_t* instr) {
4605 return v8::internal::Assembler::ConstantPoolSizeAt(
4606 reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Instruction*>(instr));
4607}
4608
4609void Disassembler::Disassemble(FILE* file, uint8_t* start, uint8_t* end,
4610 UnimplementedOpcodeAction) {
4611 v8::internal::Decoder<v8::internal::DispatchingDecoderVisitor> decoder;
4612 v8::internal::PrintDisassembler disasm(file);
4613 decoder.AppendVisitor(&disasm);
4614
4615 for (uint8_t* pc = start; pc < end; pc += v8::internal::kInstrSize) {
4616 decoder.Decode(reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Instruction*>(pc));
4617 }
4618}
4619
4620} // namespace disasm
